 guideline is to help the Nitro team have an understanding to the different button uses through out Nitro. If used correctly, it will create a more comprehensive interface that the end user can understand from instinct.</h2>"},"block_settings":[]},{"name":"Guidelines","type":"guidelines","region":2,"showOnDefault":true,"preview_image":"banner.png","content":{"text_block":"<h3>Guidelines</h3><p><span>These guidelines are the framework upon which we have built our system for how buttons are used in Nitro.</span><br></p>"},"block_settings":[]},{"name":"Guidelines","type":"guidelines","region":2,"showOnDefault":true,"preview_image":"banner.png","content":{"text_block":"<h3>Best Practices<br></h3><p>Buttons should:</p><ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;\"><li>Be clearly and accurately labeled.</li><li>Lead with strong, actionable verbs.</li><li>Use established button colors appropriately. For example, only use a red button for an action that's difficult or impossible to undo.</li><li>Prioritize the most important actions. Too many calls to action can cause confustion and make users unsure of what to do next.</li><li>Be positioned in consistent locations in the interface.</li></ul>"},"block_settings":[]},{"name":"Guidelines","type":"guidelines","region":2,"showOnDefault":true,"preview_image":"banner.png","content":{"text_block":"<h3>Do's and Don'ts</h3>"},"block_settings":[]},{"name":"Utlity Grid","type":"utility_grid","region":2,"showOnDefault":true,"preview_image":"banner.png","content":{"text_block_1":"<p>Buttons should be scannable—avoid unnecessary words and articles such as the, an, or a. Also try to avoid punctuation marks like commas and periods. NO more than three words.</p>","text_block_2":"<p><button class=\"btn btn-default dropdown-toggle\">Basic <span class=\"fa fa-angle-down\">&nbsp;</span></button></p><p>Basic Default with dropdown menu option</p>","text_block_3":"<p><button class=\"btn btn-default\"><em class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\">&nbsp;</em> Basic</button></p><p>Basic Default with icon signifier</p>","text_block_4":"<p><a class=\"btn btn-default\">Basic</a></p><p>Basic&nbsp;Default</p>"},"block_settings":[{"group":"Content","settings":[{"id":"col_count","label":"Column Count","type":"select_name","placeholder":"Three: .col-4/.col-4/.col-4","value":"12","options":[{"title":"One: .col-12","id":"12","$$hashKey":"object:780"},{"title":"Two: .col-6/.col-6","id":"6/6","$$hashKey":"object:781"},{"title":"Two: .col-4/.col-8","id":"4/8","$$hashKey":"object:782"},{"title":"Two: .col-8/.col-4","id":"8/4","$$hashKey":"object:783"},{"title":"Three: .col-4/.col-4/.col-4","id":"4/4/4","$$hashKey":"object:784"},{"title":"Four: .col-3/.col-3/.col-3/.col-3","id":"3/3/3/3","$$hashKey":"object:785"}],"required":false,"$$hashKey":"object:768"}],"$$hashKey":"object:766"}]},{"name":"Best Practice","type":"best_practices","region":2,"showOnDefault":true,"preview_image":"banner.png","content":{"text_block_1":"<div class=\"card-block-separator border-top-0 pt-0\"><span class=\"fa fa-check text-power-green\">&nbsp;</span> Create New Email</div><div class=\"card-block-separator border-top-0 border-bottom-0 pb-0\"><span class=\"fa fa-check text-power-green\">&nbsp;</span> Add New Event</div>","text_block_2":"<div class=\"card-block-separator border-top-0 pt-0\"><span class=\"fa fa-times text-power-red\">&nbsp;</span> Create a new email</div><div class=\"card-block-separator border-top-0 border-bottom-0 pb-0\"><span class=\"fa fa-times text-power-red\">&nbsp;</span> Add a New Corporate Event.</div>"},"block_settings":[]},{"name":"Utlity Grid","type":"utility_grid","region":2,"showOnDefault":true,"preview_image":"banner.png","content":{"text_block_1":"<p>Buttons should always lead with a strong verb that encourages action. To provide enough context to the end users use the {verb}+{noun} format on buttons except in the case of common actions like Save, Close, Cancel, or OK. Keep the actions short as possible without losing direction.</p>","text_blo